      <reaction compartment="compartment_81347" fast="false" id="reaction_2484822" metaid="metaid_58" name="Kinetochore assembly" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The kinetochore assembly on centromeres of replicated chromosomes is completed by mitotic prometaphase. Some kinetochore components are associated with centromeres throughout the cell cycle while others associate with centromeres during mitosis. The sequential kinetochore assembly and kinetochore dynamics is not shown here. For a review of this process, please refer to Cheeseman and Desai 2008.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
