      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_9851946" metaid="metaid_64" name="FIRRM binds PLK1" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">FIRRM (also known as Apolo1, FINGL1-interacting regulator of recombination and mitosis, FLIP or C1orf112) colocalizes with PLK1 to kinetochores during prometaphase. The N-terminus of FIRRM (amino acids 1-176) binds to the C-terminal polo-box domain (PBD) of PLK1 (Xu et al. 2021).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
