      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_9648017" metaid="metaid_69" name="EML4 binds to microtubules" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">In interphase cells, EML4 associates with cytosolic microtubules. The interaction involves the N-terminal domain of EML4 (Pollmann et al. 2006). EML4 trimerization is needed for microtubule binding (Richards et al. 2015). EML4 binding stabilizes interphase microtubules (Houtman et al. 2007, Adib et al. 2019).</p>
        </notes>
